                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/7512: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Macgowan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-10-20T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 20, 1920—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 53, October 12, 4 p.m. Refrain from requesting Japanese protection, either
                    jointly with the other members of the Consular Corps or singly as American
                    Consul.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
